British Parliament Personal Wealth Data

Data set used in experiment to analyze the causal effect of being elected to Parliament in the United Kingdom on one's personal wealth.

MPs

Format

A data frame with 427 rows and 10 variables:

surname
character: surname of the candidate
firstname
character: first name of the candidate
party
character: party of the candidate (labour or tory)
ln.gross
numeric: log gross wealth at the time of death
ln.net
numeric: log net wealth at the time of death
yob
integer: year of birth of the candidate
yod
integer: year of death of the candidate
margin.pre
numeric: margin of the candidate’s party in the previous election
region
character: electoral region
margin
numeric: margin of victory (vote share)

Details

See QSS Table 4.8.
